text: Clinton Wesley Morgan (born July 23, 1950) is an American politician from the state of Kentucky. A member of the Republican Party, Morgan is a former member of the Kentucky House of Representatives for the 81st district. Morgan lost renomination to the Kentucky House to Deanna Frazier in the 2018 elections. He unsuccessfuly ran for the Republican nomination in the 2020 United States Senate election in Kentucky against Mitch McConnell, placing second with 5.4% of the vote. https://www.kentucky.com/news/politics- government/article230935263.html ==References== ==External links== Category:Living people Category:People from Richmond, Kentucky Category:Kentucky Republicans Category:Members of the Kentucky House of Representatives Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:1950 births Category:Candidates in the 2020 United States elections
